[Albirex Niigata FC (Singapore)]], Adachihara played for Viancone Fukushima in the regional league and Japan's College of Upward Players in Soccer after graduating from [[Ryutsu Keizai University]].\n\nAfter his contract expired with Persiba Balikpapan, Adachihara signed for Bandung-based football club, [[Persib Bandung]] on 5 October 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/id-ID/news/1387/nasional/2012/10/05/3427029/persib-sudah-dapatkan-tanda-tangan-pelatih-enam-pemain|title=Persib Sudah Dapatkan Tanda Tangan Pelatih & Enam Pemain|date=5 October 2012|publisher=goal.com|accessdate=5 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121008031747/http://www.goal.com/id-ID/news/1387/nasional/2012/10/05/3427029/persib-sudah-dapatkan-tanda-tangan-pelatih-enam-pemain#|archive-date=8 October 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Squad Persib Bandung}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Adachihara, Kenji}}\n[[Category:Albirex Niigata players]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Liga 1 (Indonesia) players]]\n[[Category:Bontang FC players]]\n[[Category:Persiba Balikpapan players]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate sportspeople in Singapore]]\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate sportspeople in Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Albirex Niigata Singapore FC players]]\n[[Category:Singapore Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-forward-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Kenji Adachihara\n| fullname    = Kenji Adachihara\n| image       =  \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1984|11|08|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Sagamihara, Kanagawa]], [[Japan]]\n| height      = {{height|m=1.76}}\